Global Food Grade Maltitol Market Insights
Food Grade Maltitol Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Food Grade Maltitol Market Overview
The global food grade maltitol market has seen considerable growth, with an estimated market value of USD 1.5 billion in 2023 and a projected CAGR of 6.2% from 2024 to 2032. Maltitol, a sugar alcohol used as a sweetener in various food products, has gained popularity due to its low-calorie content and lower glycemic index, making it a favored choice in the growing health-conscious consumer base. The demand for sugar substitutes, particularly in diabetic-friendly, low-sugar, and keto diets, continues to drive market growth. The market is increasingly being driven by a shift toward healthier eating habits and a rising preference for clean-label products, which avoid artificial sweeteners.

